Install Dart and Flutter SDK:

First head to official site : https://docs.flutter.dev/get-started/install

For macOS or Linux:
Get Flutter from the official website.
Extract the files.
Add Flutter to your system's PATH.
for mac : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VPoqbBXzGtA

For Windows:
Download Flutter from the official website. 
Run the installer.
Add Flutter to your system's PATH.
for windows : https://youtube.com/watch?v=9WT9s7jkGEQ

Set up Your IDE or Code Editor:

For Visual Studio Code:
Install the Flutter and Dart extensions from the marketplace.

For other IDEs or editors:
Follow instructions on the official Flutter documentation.

Verify Installation:
Run flutter doctor in your terminal to check your Flutter installation status and identify any missing dependencies.

you will see this
[✓] Chrome - develop for the web
[✓] Android Studio (version 2023.3)
[✓] VS Code (version 1.88.1)
[✓] Connected device (2 available)
[✓] Network resources



